          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Validation_GetAccountMeterDiscrepancy",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to identify discrepancies between account and meter records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SBMR",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema and their corresponding records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "billing",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema. It checks for account numbers and meter numbers in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SBMR",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " tables that do not have corresponding entries in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "billing",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " tables. The procedure returns two types of records: account discrepancies and meter discrepancies, each marked with a specific record type ('A' for accounts and 'M' for meters)."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
